# Tablio

Tauri v2 desktop database management app (PostgreSQL, MySQL, SQLite).

## Tech Stack

- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript + Vite
- **Backend**: Rust (Tauri)
- **Renderer**: WebKitGTK on Linux (NOT Chromium — some CSS features behave differently)
- **Fonts**: Fira Sans (UI), JetBrains Mono NF (data grid, code)

## Project Layout

- `src/components/` — React components, each with colocated `.css` file
- `src/styles/global.css` — Global styles, CSS variables, `:root` tokens, base element styles
- `src/lib/themes.ts` — 11 theme definitions (6 dark, 5 light)
- `src/lib/tauri.ts` — Tauri API bindings
- `src-tauri/` — Rust backend

## Key Conventions

- CSS: all styling via colocated `.css` files, no CSS-in-JS
- Zoom: app supports CSS zoom; context menus must divide `e.clientX`/`e.clientY` by `document.documentElement.style.zoom`
- Icons: use `lucide-react`
- Build: `unset CI && npx tauri build --bundles deb` for release .deb
